Foot & mouth disease - Bolivia (04) 20010825.2011
Date: 3 Oct 2001
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Los Tiempos 21 Sep 2001 [edited

The health emergency declared because the FMD epidemic on 13 Aug [2001 was
annuled. From 1 Oct the restrictions of movements will be lifted and
animals can be transported to other regions. During this late period a
total of 255 000 animals have been vaccinated all over the Cochabamba
region, with an estimated 87 percent coverage, said Antonio Vallejos, head
of the regional Servicio Nacional de Sanidad Agropecuaria Inocuidad Animal
(Senesag).
The emergency was declared after 24 outbreaks were detected, accounting for
70 percent of the reported at national level.
Since 13 Aug another 9 more outbreaks were detected, 2 of them concentrated
in the Oruro region, found in the Arque province.
